["To apply for withdrawal of your next-of-kin's CPF savings, you can make an appointment to visit any of our CPF Service Centres and bring along the following original documents:", '1. Medical report from an accredited doctor stating that the member lacks mental capacity permanently;
2. Lasting Power of Attorney or Court Order;
3. Trust bank account statement or passbook; and
4. Your NRIC.']

['As an appointed donee or deputy for your next-of-kin, you may apply to withdraw his CPF savings under the Reduced Life Expectancy scheme by making an appointment to visit any of our CPF Service Centres and bringing along the following original documents:', '1. Medical report from an accredited doctor stating that the member lacks mental capacity permanently;
2. Lasting Power of Attorney or Court Order;
3. Trust bank account statement or passbook; and
4. Your NRIC.']
